    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prehistoric stone tools; flakes or blades retouched to produce ragged edges probably used mostly to cut meat, but possibly also in woodworking.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
